text: Trevor Paul Moore (April 4, 1980 â€“ August 6, 2021) was an American comedian, actor and musician. He was known as one of the founding members of the New York City-based comedy group the Whitest Kids U' Know (WKUK). He also directed and starred in the comedy Miss March (2009). Moore was born in Montclair, New Jersey.
